cs.AR, cs.EM, cs.PF, cs.SY, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.AR (Architecture): The paper focuses on analyzing the power, performance, and efficiency of the RISC-V instruction set architecture, specifically targeting application-class functionality. 
- cs.EM (Embedded Systems): The paper discusses the implementation of the RISC-V core in a 22nm FDSOI technology, which is commonly used in embedded systems. 
- cs.PF (Performance): The paper provides a detailed analysis of the performance of the RISC-V core, including its energy efficiency and compute performance. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the interplay between functionality required for application-class execution and energy cost, which is relevant to systems and control. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper mentions the support for the Linux OS and its application environment, which is related to programming languages.
